\f0\fs36 \cf0 # SNAPBRAND Quick Start Guide (Prisma + PostgreSQL)\
\
Get your SNAPBRAND app up and running in 10 minutes.\
\
## 1. Install Dependencies \uc0\u9989  Done!\
\
Dependencies are already installed. Verify:\
```bash\
npm list | grep prisma\
npm list | grep next-auth\
```\
\
## 2. Set Up PostgreSQL Database\
\
### Fastest Option: Railway.app\
\
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app)\
2. Sign up (free account)\
3. Click "New Project" \uc0\u8594  Add "PostgreSQL"\
4. Copy the `DATABASE_URL` from the PostgreSQL card\
5. Paste into `.env.local`\
\
**Takes 2 minutes!**\
\
### Alternative: Local PostgreSQL\
\
```bash\
brew install postgresql@15\
brew services start postgresql@15\
createdb snapbrand\
```\
\
Then set in `.env.local`:\
```bash\
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/snapbrand\
```\
\
## 3. Configure Environment Variables\
\
Copy template and fill in all values:\
```bash\
cp .env.local.example .env.local\
```\
\
Minimum required:\
```bash\
# Database\
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...\
\
# NextAuth\
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=<run: openssl rand -base64 32>\
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000\
\
# Google OAuth (optional, but recommended)\
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=\
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=\
\
# Stripe, OpenAI, Vercel Blob (if using generation features)\
...\
```\
\
## 4. Set Up Database Tables\
\
Push Prisma schema to your database:\
```bash\
npx prisma db push\
```\
\
This creates all tables automatically!\
\
## 5. (Optional) Set Up Google OAuth\
\
1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com)\
2. Create new project\
3. Enable Google+ API\
4. Create OAuth credentials:\
   - Type: Web application\
   - Authorized redirect URI: `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google`\
5. Copy Client ID and Secret to `.env.local`\
\
## 6. Run the App\
\
```bash\
npm run dev\
```\
\
Visit `http://localhost:3000`\
\
## 7. Test Everything\
\
### Email/Password Login\
- Click "Sign Up"\
- Enter any email and password\
- Demo password: `password123` (shown on login page)\
\
### View Database\
```bash\
npx prisma studio\
```\
\
Opens UI at `http://localhost:5555` - see all your users and assets!\
\
### Test Generation (if you add your keys)\
- Add `OPENAI_API_KEY` and `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN`\
- Go to dashboard\
- Try generating a brand asset\
\
## Migration to Production\
\
When deploying to Vercel:\
\
1. Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard\
2. Vercel will auto-run migrations\
3. Update Stripe webhooks to production URL\
4. Update Google OAuth redirect URIs\
\
See [PRISMA_SETUP.md](./PRISMA_SETUP.md) for detailed production guide.\
\
## Database Schema\
\
The app creates these tables automatically:\
\
- **User** - User accounts and Pro membership status\
- **Account** - OAuth provider accounts\
- **Session** - NextAuth sessions\
- **GeneratedAsset** - User's generated brand assets\
- **VerificationToken** - Email verification tokens\
\
View/edit with: `npx prisma studio`\
\
## Troubleshooting\
\
### "Can't reach database server"\
- Check DATABASE_URL is correct\
- Verify database is running\
- Test connection: `psql YOUR_DATABASE_URL`\
\
### "Prisma client not generated"\
```bash\
npx prisma generate\
```\
\
### "Migration failed"\
```bash\
# Reset database (deletes all data)\
npx prisma migrate reset\
```\
\
### "NextAuth not working"\
- Set `NEXTAUTH_SECRET`\
- Set `NEXTAUTH_URL` correctly\
- Restart dev server\
\
